I used to watch this show - I remember watching the season Kai was on... I always thought those sports bras were horrible -- zero support and ridiculous. I think they all should wear their t-shirts to weigh in. The intense pressure, crash dieting and insane workout schedule can work for some people but for the majority, I doubt it's all that motivating and can't possibly be healthy. I think the show has gotten really mean spirited -- I originally got a lot of good food/workout tips when it first aired with Bob and Jillian but now it's just mean spirited """"entertainment"""".

Jenifer, I was privileged to tour s animal hospital in San Diego and meet with many of their staff. They return Seal pups and sea lion pups after they rehabilitate them. This occurs monthly. They are a truly dedicated staff and are so excited to see those animals returned to the wild. To see them interact with the animals assures me they care, a LOT. I could not see some brown pelicans being rehabbed there as they didn't want them bonding with humans or causing anxiety.
